name: fhir
documentation: All definitions associated with the base FHIR Specification

definitions.name: Address
definitions.documentation: An address expressed using postal conventions (as opposed to GPS or other location definition formats).  This data type may be used to convey addresses for use in delivering mail as well as for visiting locations which might not be valid for mail delivery.  There are a variety of postal address formats defined around the world.

definitions.name: Age
definitions.documentation: A duration of time during which an organism (or a process) has existed.

definitions.name: Annotation
definitions.documentation: A  text note which also  contains information about who made the statement and when.

definitions.name: Attachment
definitions.documentation: For referring to data content defined in other formats.

definitions.name: BackboneElement
definitions.documentation: Base definition for all elements that are defined inside a resource - but not those in a data type.

definitions.name: BackboneType
definitions.documentation: Base definition for the few data types that are allowed to carry modifier extensions.

definitions.name: Base
definitions.documentation: Base definition for all types defined in FHIR type system.

definitions.name: CodeableConcept
definitions.documentation: A concept that may be defined by a formal reference to a terminology or ontology or may be provided by text.

definitions.name: CodeableReference
definitions.documentation: A reference to a resource (by instance), or instead, a reference to a cencept defined in a terminology or ontology (by class).

definitions.name: Coding
definitions.documentation: A reference to a code defined by a terminology system.

definitions.name: ContactDetail
definitions.documentation: Specifies contact information for a person or organization.

definitions.name: ContactPoint
definitions.documentation: Details for all kinds of technology mediated contact points for a person or organization, including telephone, email, etc.

definitions.name: Contributor
definitions.documentation: A contributor to the content of a knowledge asset, including authors, editors, reviewers, and endorsers.

definitions.name: Count
definitions.documentation: A measured amount (or an amount that can potentially be measured). Note that measured amounts include amounts that are not precisely quantified, including amounts involving arbitrary units and floating currencies.

definitions.name: DataRequirement
definitions.documentation: Describes a required data item for evaluation in terms of the type of data, and optional code or date-based filters of the data.

definitions.name: DataType
definitions.documentation: The base class for all re-useable types defined as part of the FHIR Specification.

definitions.name: Distance
definitions.documentation: A length - a value with a unit that is a physical distance.

definitions.name: Dosage
definitions.documentation: Indicates how the medication is/was taken or should be taken by the patient.

definitions.name: Duration
definitions.documentation: A length of time.

definitions.name: Element
definitions.documentation: Base definition for all elements in a resource.

definitions.name: ElementDefinition
definitions.documentation: Captures constraints on each element within the resource, profile, or extension.

definitions.name: Expression
definitions.documentation: A expression that is evaluated in a specified context and returns a value. The context of use of the expression must specify the context in which the expression is evaluated, and how the result of the expression is used.

definitions.name: Extension
definitions.documentation: Optional Extension Element - found in all resources.

definitions.name: HumanName
definitions.documentation: A human's name with the ability to identify parts and usage.

definitions.name: Identifier
definitions.documentation: An identifier - identifies some entity uniquely and unambiguously. Typically this is used for business identifiers.

definitions.name: MarketingStatus
definitions.documentation: The marketing status describes the date when a medicinal product is actually put on the market or the date as of which it is no longer available.

definitions.name: Meta
definitions.documentation: The metadata about a resource. This is content in the resource that is maintained by the infrastructure. Changes to the content might not always be associated with version changes to the resource.

definitions.name: Money
definitions.documentation: An amount of economic utility in some recognized currency.

definitions.name: Narrative
definitions.documentation: A human-readable summary of the resource conveying the essential clinical and business information for the resource.

definitions.name: OrderedDistribution
definitions.documentation: An ordered list (distribution) of statistics.

definitions.name: ParameterDefinition
definitions.documentation: The parameters to the module. This collection specifies both the input and output parameters. Input parameters are provided by the caller as part of the $evaluate operation. Output parameters are included in the GuidanceResponse.

definitions.name: Period
definitions.documentation: A time period defined by a start and end date and optionally time.

definitions.name: Population
definitions.documentation: A populatioof people with some set of grouping criteria.

definitions.name: PrimitiveType
definitions.documentation: The base type for all re-useable types defined that have a simple property.

definitions.name: ProdCharacteristic
definitions.documentation: The marketing status describes the date when a medicinal product is actually put on the market or the date as of which it is no longer available.

definitions.name: ProductShelfLife
definitions.documentation: The shelf-life and storage information for a medicinal product item or container can be described using this class.

definitions.name: Quantity
definitions.documentation: A measured amount (or an amount that can potentially be measured). Note that measured amounts include amounts that are not precisely quantified, including amounts involving arbitrary units and floating currencies.

definitions.name: Range
definitions.documentation: A set of ordered Quantities defined by a low and high limit.

definitions.name: Ratio
definitions.documentation: A relationship of two Quantity values - expressed as a numerator and a denominator.

definitions.name: RatioRange
definitions.documentation: A range of ratios expressed as a low and high numerator and a denominator.

definitions.name: Reference
definitions.documentation: A reference from one resource to another.

definitions.name: RelatedArtifact
definitions.documentation: Related artifacts such as additional documentation, justification, or bibliographic references.

definitions.name: SampledData
definitions.documentation: A series of measurements taken by a device, with upper and lower limits. There may be more than one dimension in the data.

definitions.name: Signature
definitions.documentation: A signature along with supporting context. The signature may be a digital signature that is cryptographic in nature, or some other signature acceptable to the domain. This other signature may be as simple as a graphical image representing a hand-written signature, or a signature ceremony Different signature approaches have different utilities.

definitions.name: Statistic
definitions.documentation: A fact or piece of data from a  study of a large quantity of numerical data.  A mathematical or quantified characteristic of a group of observations.

definitions.name: Timing
definitions.documentation: Specifies an event that may occur multiple times. Timing schedules are used to record when things are planned, expected or requested to occur. The most common usage is in dosage instructions for medications. They are also used when planning care of various kinds, and may be used for reporting the schedule to which past regular activities were carried out.

definitions.name: TriggerDefinition
definitions.documentation: A description of a triggering event. Triggering events can be named events, data events, or periodic, as determined by the type element.

definitions.name: UsageContext
definitions.documentation: Specifies clinical/business/etc. metadata that can be used to retrieve, index and/or categorize an artifact. This metadata can either be specific to the applicable population (e.g., age category, DRG) or the specific context of care (e.g., venue, care setting, provider of care).

definitions.name: base64Binary
definitions.documentation: A stream of bytes

definitions.name: boolean
definitions.documentation: Value of "true" or "false"

definitions.name: canonical
definitions.documentation: A URI that is a reference to a canonical URL on a FHIR resource

definitions.name: code
definitions.documentation: A string which has at least one character and no leading or trailing whitespace and where there is no whitespace other than single spaces in the contents

definitions.name: date
definitions.documentation: A date or partial date (e.g. just year or year + month). There is no UTC offset. The format is a union of the schema types gYear, gYearMonth and date.  Dates SHALL be valid dates.

definitions.name: dateTime
definitions.documentation: A date, date-time or partial date (e.g. just year or year + month).  If hours and minutes are specified, a UTC offset SHALL be populated. The format is a union of the schema types gYear, gYearMonth, date and dateTime. Seconds must be provided due to schema type constraints but may be zero-filled and may be ignored.                 Dates SHALL be valid dates.

definitions.name: decimal
definitions.documentation: A rational number with implicit precision

definitions.name: id
definitions.documentation: Any combination of letters, numerals, "-" and ".", with a length limit of 64 characters.  (This might be an integer, an unprefixed OID, UUID or any other identifier pattern that meets these constraints.)  Ids are case-insensitive.

definitions.name: instant
definitions.documentation: An instant in time - known at least to the second

definitions.name: integer
definitions.documentation: A whole number

definitions.name: integer64
definitions.documentation: A very large whole number

definitions.name: markdown
definitions.documentation: A string that may contain Github Flavored Markdown syntax for optional processing by a mark down presentation engine

definitions.name: oid
definitions.documentation: An OID represented as a URI

definitions.name: positiveInt
definitions.documentation: An integer with a value that is positive (e.g. >0)

definitions.name: string
definitions.documentation: A sequence of Unicode characters

definitions.name: time
definitions.documentation: A time during the day, with no date specified

definitions.name: unsignedInt
definitions.documentation: An integer with a value that is not negative (e.g. >= 0)

definitions.name: uri
definitions.documentation: String of characters used to identify a name or a resource

definitions.name: url
definitions.documentation: A URI that is a literal reference

definitions.name: uuid
definitions.documentation: A UUID, represented as a URI
